<div class="asset" style="margin-top:4rem; border-top:1px solid #333; padding-top:3rem;">
<h2>The Point</h2>

<p>995 lines of code. Five signals. None of them definitive. All of them together create a picture that is more useful than any single data source.</p>

<p>The intelligence layer does not make decisions. It does not approve or reject. It does not score people on a scale that determines their worthiness. It answers one question for the agent: given what we know right now, what is the most useful thing to say next?</p>

<p>A human leasing agent does this intuitively. They hear a Gary area code and know this person works at the steel mill or the casino. They see an Englewood address and know to ask about vouchers early. They notice confident language about credit and relax their pitch. The intelligence layer is that intuition, extracted into five functions that run in under two seconds.</p>

<p>The lead does not know any of this is happening. They texted "Is the 2br still available?" and got back a response that felt like it was written by someone who understood their situation. That is the entire point.</p>

</div>
